"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Fixed the fake `kernel32` callback calling convention and amended the commit.\\n\\nCause:\\n- The fake `NativeLibrary` must be cached under the Windows `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION` key because that is how JNA looks up `Kernel32` functions.\\n- But the actual callback is executed on Linux, where invoking a JNA `Function` with calling convention `63` fails with `Unrecognized calling convention: 63`.\\n\\nFix:\\n- Keep the cache key using `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION`.\\n- Create the callback-backed `Function` with `Function.C_CONVENTION`, so it can be invoked on Linux.\\n\\nUpdated commit:\\n- `9ef9a3b340 Add JNA Factory proxy coverage test`\\n\\nWorking tree is clean. I did not run tests.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2e028729081a290a0ea17e7c06a29\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 356, \"output\": 167, \"cacheRead\": 71168, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 71691, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777524774272, \"responseId\": \"resp_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2e027804c81a29ed025569f222cf7\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Fixed the fake `kernel32` callback calling convention and amended the commit.\\n\\nCause:\\n- The fake `NativeLibrary` must be cached under the Windows `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION` key because that is how JNA looks up `Kernel32` functions.\\n- But the actual callback is executed on Linux, where invoking a JNA `Function` with calling convention `63` fails with `Unrecognized calling convention: 63`.\\n\\nFix:\\n- Keep the cache key using `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION`.\\n- Crea